OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1775113301
OL,3,C'Awful' April: Which household bills
OL,4,Care set to rise and what support is
OL,5,Cthere?
OL,7,FHowever, the decrease is lower than
OL,8,Fthe average #150 cut to bills pledged
OL,9,Fby Chancellor Rachel Reeves in
OL,10,FNovember's Autumn budget, when she
OL,11,Fmoved 75% of the cost of the
OL,12,Frenewables obligation from household
OL,13,Fbills onto general taxation and
OL,14,Fscrapped the energy company obligation
OL,15,F(Eco) scheme.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/21
