OL,3,C'Awful' April: Which household bills
OL,4,Care set to rise and what support is
OL,5,Cthere?
OL,7,FIn the meantime, consumer groups have
OL,8,Furged households to send in meter
OL,9,Freadings ahead of Wednesday's changes
OL,10,Fto ensure their energy usage is billed
OL,11,Fat the lowest possible rate, and
OL,12,Finvestigate fixed rate deals.
OL,14,FCouncil tax
OL,16,FAcross England, the average Band D
OL,17,Fcouncil tax in 2026/27 will be #2,392
OL,18,F` an increase of #111 or 4.9% from
OL,19,F2025-26, according to the Ministry of
OL,20,FHousing, Communities & Local
OL,21,FGovernment.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/21
