OL,3,C'Awful' April: Which household bills
OL,4,Care set to rise and what support is
OL,5,Cthere?
OL,7,FThe figures include all additional
OL,8,Fcharges, including adult social care,
OL,9,Fparish precepts and costs levied by
OL,10,Fpolice, fire and regional authorities
OL,11,Fwhere appropriate.
OL,13,FIn Scotland, households will see rises
OL,14,Fof between 4% and 10%, whilst in Wales
OL,15,Fbills will go up by 4% to 5%.
OL,17,FIt is the fourth year in a row that
OL,18,Fthe England-wide increase has averaged
OL,19,Faround 5%, meanwhile the increases in
OL,20,FScotland and Wales are generally lower
OL,21,Fthan previous years.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/21
