OL,3,C'Awful' April: Which household bills
OL,4,Care set to rise and what support is
OL,5,Cthere?
OL,7,FBroadband and mobile phones
OL,9,FBoth broadband and mobile phone rates
OL,10,Fare rising due to annual,
OL,11,Fcontractually permitted increases
OL,12,Fdesigned to match the rising costs of
OL,13,Fdoing business and investing in
OL,14,Fnetwork infrastructure.
OL,16,FMany contracts include a clause
OL,17,Fstating that monthly bills will
OL,18,Fincrease every April by the Consumer
OL,19,FPrice Index (CPI) rate published in
OL,20,FJanuary, plus an additional 3.9%. The
OL,21,FCPI currently stands at 3.2%.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/21
